The Lemen Islands is the core zone of the Nan'ao Provincial Nature Reserve for Migratory Birds. Every summer, the black-naped terns, along with their neighbors, the bridled terns, great crested terns and Pacific reef-egrets, breed here together. About 'Journeys in Nature': Nan'ao Series Nan'ao Island in Guangdong Province is a rare habitat of greenery on the Tropic of Cancer. In June, the southeastern monsoon brings warm, moist air to the island, nurturing all lifeforms: from ancient fig trees and newborn black-naped terns to mysterious undersea creatures and medical herbs, which bestow Nan'ao Island with many stories. For more: Guangdong Nan'ao Series | Episode 1: Windy Island Guangdong Nan'ao Series | Episode 2: Reef Ninja Guangdong Nan'ao Series | Episode 3: Brown-winged dancer (Cover image via a screenshot) (If you want to contribute and have specific expertise, please contact us at nature@cgtn.com.)